        <h3>Then just run it</h3>
        <p>Itervox polls your tracker, claims new issues, spawns agents in isolated Git worktrees, and submits PRs when the work is done. Every step is logged and visible in the dashboard or terminal UI.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Polls Linear or GitHub Issues on a configurable interval</li>
          <li>Spawns one agent per issue in isolated worktrees</li>
          <li>Retries on failure with exponential backoff</li>
          <li>Transitions issue state on success or failure</li>
          <li>Live dashboard at localhost:8090</li>
