<!-- ===== 9. Agent Profiles + Hit Rate Limits ===== -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header">
      <div class="section-label">Profiles</div>
      <h2 class="section-heading">Agent Profiles</h2>
      <p class="section-sub">Define named agent profiles with per-profile commands, backends, and role prompts. Profile prompts support Liquid template variables &mdash; reference issue data like <code class="mono" style="font-size:13px; color:var(--accent);">{"{{ issue.identifier }}"}</code> and <code class="mono" style="font-size:13px; color:var(--accent);">{"{{ issue.title }}"}</code> directly in your role descriptions.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="usecase-profiles" style="margin-bottom: 48px;">
      <div class="profile-card">
        <div class="profile-header">
          <div class="profile-dot" style="background: var(--accent);"></div>
          <div class="profile-name">backend</div>
          <div class="profile-runner">claude</div>
        </div>
        <div class="profile-yaml">
          <div><span style="color:var(--accent-strong);">command:</span> claude</div>
          <div><span style="color:var(--accent-strong);">prompt:</span> "Backend specialist.<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;Focus on Go, APIs, DB."</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="profile-card">
        <div class="profile-header">
          <div class="profile-dot" style="background: var(--teal);"></div>
          <div class="profile-name">backend-fallback</div>
          <div class="profile-runner">codex</div>
        </div>
        <div class="profile-yaml">
          <div><span style="color:var(--teal);">command:</span> codex</div>
          <div><span style="color:var(--teal);">prompt:</span> "Backend specialist.<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;Focus on Go, APIs, DB."</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="usecase">
      <div class="usecase-label">Use case</div>
      <h3 class="usecase-heading">Hit rate limits? Just reassign.</h3>
      <p class="usecase-desc">Create named agent profiles with different runners. When one provider hits limits, drag issues to another profile in the Agent Board &mdash; no config changes, no restarts.</p>

      <div class="usecase-flow">
        <div class="flow-step flow-step--problem">
          <div class="flow-step-num">1</div>
          <div class="flow-step-title" style="color: var(--danger);">Rate limited</div>
          <div class="flow-step-detail">Claude API returns 429<br/>Agent paused</div>
        </div>
        <div class="flow-arrow">&rarr;</div>
        <div class="flow-step">
          <div class="flow-step-num">2</div>
          <div class="flow-step-title">Open Agent Board</div>
          <div class="flow-step-detail">Dashboard &rarr; Agents view<br/>See issues per profile</div>
        </div>
        <div class="flow-arrow">&rarr;</div>
        <div class="flow-step">
          <div class="flow-step-num">3</div>
          <div class="flow-step-title">Drag to reassign</div>
          <div class="flow-step-detail">Move issue from<br/>&ldquo;claude&rdquo; to &ldquo;codex&rdquo; column</div>
        </div>
        <div class="flow-arrow">&rarr;</div>
        <div class="flow-step flow-step--solution">
          <div class="flow-step-num">4</div>
          <div class="flow-step-title" style="color: var(--success);">Resumes instantly</div>
          <div class="flow-step-detail">Agent picks up work<br/>with Codex backend</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ===== 10. Human in the Loop ===== -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header">
      <div class="section-label">Human in the Loop</div>
      <h2 class="section-heading">Autonomous, not unsupervised</h2>
      <p class="section-sub">Agents do the work. You stay in control at every checkpoint.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="obs-grid">
      <div style="background:var(--bg-soft); border:1px solid var(--line); border-radius:var(--radius-md); padding:28px 24px;">
        <div style="font-size:24px; margin-bottom:12px;">&#128269;</div>
        <div style="font-size:16px; font-weight:600; margin-bottom:6px;">AI Code Review</div>
        <p style="font-size:13px; color:var(--text-secondary); line-height:1.6;">Configure a <code style="font-size:11px; background:var(--bg-elevated); padding:1px 4px; border-radius:3px;">reviewer_prompt</code> and trigger a second agent to review the PR on the correct branch. The reviewer uses the same runner and profile as the original worker.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="background:var(--bg-soft); border:1px solid var(--line); border-radius:var(--radius-md); padding:28px 24px;">
        <div style="font-size:24px; margin-bottom:12px;">&#9995;</div>
        <div style="font-size:16px; font-weight:600; margin-bottom:6px;">Agent Asks for Help</div>
        <p style="font-size:13px; color:var(--text-secondary); line-height:1.6;">When an agent needs human input, it pauses and posts a comment directly on the Linear or GitHub issue. Reply from the dashboard or from your tracker &mdash; the agent picks up your response and resumes automatically.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="background:var(--bg-soft); border:1px solid var(--line); border-radius:var(--radius-md); padding:28px 24px;">
        <div style="font-size:24px; margin-bottom:12px;">&#9989;</div>
        <div style="font-size:16px; font-weight:600; margin-bottom:6px;">You Merge the PR</div>
        <p style="font-size:13px; color:var(--text-secondary); line-height:1.6;">Agents submit PRs and post a session summary as a comment &mdash; they never merge. PR links are automatically commented on the tracker issue. Your team reviews and merges when ready.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

